<section id="express" class="info">
    <figure>
        <h1 class="dates" id="limelight">1900s-1920s</h1>
    </figure>
    <div class="title">
        <h3 id="pd-bold-italic">EXPRESSIONISM</h3>
        <p class="right" id="os-bold">Expressionism emerged in Germany in the early 20th century in part as a
            reaction to impressionism. Similarly to
            Post-Impressionism, Expressionism focuses on the artist's inner feelings and emotions, and not on the
            external reality.
            It is recognizable by its use of bold and exaggerated colors and lines, and distorted forms to express
            different
            emotions like anger, fear and alienation.</p>
    </div>
</section>

